                        <h3 class=3D"c-article__sub-heading" id=3D"Sec9">Ex=
ample: a meta-analysis of Stead et al. (2013)</h3><p>This section illustrat=
es the theory of Sections =E2=80=9C<a data-track=3D"click" data-track-label=
=3D"link" data-track-action=3D"section anchor" href=3D"https://link.springe=
r.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#Sec4">The mean and variance of <i>Q=
</i>
                           </a>=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9C<a data-track=3D"clic=
k" data-track-label=3D"link" data-track-action=3D"section anchor" href=3D"h=
ttps://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#Sec5">Estimating=
 the moments and distribution of <b><i>Q</i></b>
                              <sub>
                      <b><i>LOR</i></b>
                    </sub>
                           </a>=E2=80=9D and gives an indication of the imp=
rovement in accuracy of the homogeneity test. The calculations can be perfo=
rmed using our computer program (Additional files <a data-track=3D"click" d=
ata-track-label=3D"link" data-track-action=3D"supplementary material anchor=
" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#MOESM=
1">1</a>, <a data-track=3D"click" data-track-label=3D"link" data-track-acti=
on=3D"supplementary material anchor" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/arti=
cle/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#MOESM2">2</a> and <a data-track=3D"click" dat=
a-track-label=3D"link" data-track-action=3D"supplementary material anchor" =
href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#MOESM3"=
>3</a>).</p><p>We use the data from the review by Stead et al. [<a data-tra=
ck=3D"click" data-track-action=3D"reference anchor" data-track-label=3D"lin=
k" data-test=3D"citation-ref" aria-label=3D"Reference 25" title=3D"Stead LF=
, Buitrago D, Preciado N, Sanchez G, Hartmann-Boyce J, Lancaster T. Physici=
an advice for smoking cessation. Cochrane Database Syst Rev. 2013; 5. Art. =
No.: CD000165.=20
                    http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD0=
00165.pub4/full
                   =20
                 =20
                        " href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186=
/s12874-015-0034-x#ref-CR25" id=3D"ref-link-section-d57159360e6056">25</a>]=
 of clinical trials on the use of physician advice for smoking cessation. C=
omparison 03.01.04 [<a data-track=3D"click" data-track-action=3D"reference =
anchor" data-track-label=3D"link" data-test=3D"citation-ref" aria-label=3D"=
Reference 25" title=3D"Stead LF, Buitrago D, Preciado N, Sanchez G, Hartman=
n-Boyce J, Lancaster T. Physician advice for smoking cessation. Cochrane Da=
tabase Syst Rev. 2013; 5. Art. No.: CD000165.=20
                    http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/14651858.CD0=
00165.pub4/full
                   =20
                 =20
                        " href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186=
/s12874-015-0034-x#ref-CR25" id=3D"ref-link-section-d57159360e6059">25</a>]=
, p.65 considered the subgroup of interventions involving only one visit. W=
e use odds ratio in our analysis below although relative risk was used in t=
he original review. The first version of the review was published in 2001. =
Update 2, published in 2004, included 17 studies for this comparison. Summa=
ry data and the results from the standard analysis of these 17 trials are f=
ound in Figure <a data-track=3D"click" data-track-label=3D"link" data-track=
-action=3D"figure anchor" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186=
/s12874-015-0034-x#Fig6">6</a>, produced by the R package meta [<a data-tra=
ck=3D"click" data-track-action=3D"reference anchor" data-track-label=3D"lin=
k" data-test=3D"citation-ref" aria-label=3D"Reference 26" title=3D"Schwarze=
r G. meta, v.1.5-0. CRAN 2010. R package. Fixed and random effects meta-ana=
lysis. Functions for tests of bias, forest and funnel plot." href=3D"https:=
//link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#ref-CR26" id=3D"ref-l=
ink-section-d57159360e6065">26</a>]. Note that meta does not add 1/2 to the=
 number of events in calculation of the log-odds, and therefore calculates =
the standard statistic <i>Q</i>
                           <sub>
                    <i>stand</i>
                  </sub> for the test of homogeneity.
</p><div class=3D"c-article-section__figure js-c-reading-companion-figures-=
