                        <h3 class=3D"c-article__sub-heading" id=3D"Sec15">B=
.2 Information about formulas for mean and variance of <i>Q</i>
                           <sub>
                    <i>LOR</i>
                  </sub>
                        </h3><p>In this appendix we present additional info=
rmation concerning the data and methods that entered into Equations <a data=
-track=3D"click" data-track-label=3D"link" data-track-action=3D"equation an=
chor" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#E=
qu6">6</a> and <a data-track=3D"click" data-track-label=3D"link" data-track=
-action=3D"equation anchor" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/10.11=
86/s12874-015-0034-x#Equ7">7</a> which provide formulas for estimating the =
mean and variance of <i>Q</i>
                           <sub>
                    <i>LOR</i>
                  </sub> under the null hypothesis of equal odds ratios. Th=
e data for Equation <a data-track=3D"click" data-track-label=3D"link" data-=
track-action=3D"equation anchor" href=3D"https://link.springer.com/article/=
10.1186/s12874-015-0034-x#Equ6">6</a> include 648 parameter combinations in=
 which all <i>K</i> studies had identical parameters. The parameters are: <=
i>K</i>=3D 5, 10, 20, 40; <i>N</i>=3D 90, 150, 210; <i>q</i>=3D 1/3, 1/2, 2=
/3; <i>p</i>
                           <sub>
                    <i>C</i>
                  </sub>=3D0.1, 0.2, 0.4; and <i>=CE=B8</i>=3D 0, 0.5, 1, 1=
.5, 2, 3. The simulations for <i>K</i>=3D40 were replicated 1,000 times, an=
d the other simulations were replicated 10,000 times.</p><p>For each combin=
ation of parameters, we calculated an estimate of the mean of <i>Q</i>
                           <sub>
                    <i>LOR</i>
                  </sub> (to be denoted simply <i>Q</i> in this section) us=
ing the theoretical expansion of Kulinskaya et al. [<a data-track=3D"click"=
 data-track-action=3D"reference anchor" data-track-label=3D"link" data-test=
=3D"citation-ref" aria-label=3D"Reference 10" title=3D"Kulinskaya E, Dollin=
ger MB, Bj=C3=B8rkest=C3=B8l K. On the moments of Cochran=E2=80=99s Q stati=
stic under the null hypothesis, with application to the meta-analysis of ri=
sk difference. Res Synth Methods. 2011; 2:254=E2=80=9370.=20
                    doi:10.1002/jrsm.54
                   =20
                 =20
