/s12874-015-0034-x#ref-CR10" id=3D"ref-link-section-d57159360e8667">10</a>]=
 is reproduced at the end of this appendix. In the formulas below, we use t=
he notation <span class=3D"mathjax-tex">\(\Theta _{i}=3D\widehat {\theta }_=
{i}-\theta _{i}\)</span> and <span class=3D"mathjax-tex">\(Z_{i}=3D\widehat=
 {\zeta }_{i}-\zeta _{i}\)</span>; also, we express the weight estimators a=
s functions of the parameter estimators <span class=3D"mathjax-tex">\(\wide=
hat {w}_{i}=3Df_{i}(\widehat {\theta }_{i}, \widehat {\zeta }_{i})\)</span>=
. The theoretical weights under the null hypothesis are then <i>w</i>
